.TH "sys_sigprocmask" 9 "sys_sigprocmask" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sys_sigprocmask \- examine and change blocked signals
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" sys_sigprocmask
.BI "(int how "  ","
.BI "old_sigset_t __user * nset "  ","
.BI "old_sigset_t __user * oset "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "how" 12
whether to add, remove, or set signals
.IP "nset" 12
signals to add or remove (if non-null)
.IP "oset" 12
previous value of signal mask if non-null
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Some platforms have their own version with special arguments;
others support only sys_rt_sigprocmask.
